cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY

The paper deals with game theory and network security, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making), as the paper explicitly mentions modeling the interaction between the smart jammer and LTE network as a game. The second likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the vulnerability of LTE networks to denial-of-service and loss-of-service attacks. The third likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with security strategies for both players. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with incomplete information. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with constructing efficient suboptimal strategies for both players.
